title: Geotechnical Engineer

ambitionBoxData.Title: Fugro Survey India Reviews by Employees

jobDescription:
Fugro Survey (India) Pvt. Ltd is looking for Geotechnical Engineer to join our dynamic team and embark on a rewarding career journey. A geotechnical engineer specializes in the analysis, design, and construction of structures and infrastructure projects involving soil, rock, and other geologic materials. They assess the behavior of the ground and provide recommendations to ensure the stability and safety of construction projects.
 
Here are some key responsibilities and tasks of a geotechnical engineer:
 
  • Site Investigation: Geotechnical engineers conduct site investigations to understand the subsurface conditions and geologic characteristics of a site
  • This involves collecting soil and rock samples, performing geotechnical tests, and analyzing the data to determine the site's properties and behavior
  • Geotechnical Analysis: They analyze the geotechnical data to assess the stability and load-bearing capacity of the ground
  • This includes evaluating soil properties, determining slope stability, assessing foundation requirements, and analyzing the potential for settlement or soil liquefaction
  • Design Recommendations: Geotechnical engineers provide design recommendations based on their analysis to ensure the safe and reliable construction of structures
  • This may involve recommending suitable foundation types, slope stabilization measures, ground improvement techniques, or retaining wall designs
  • Geotechnical Instrumentation: They install and monitor geotechnical instrumentation to measure and analyze ground movements, soil pressures, and other parameters during and after construction
  • This data helps in assessing the performance of structures and determining any necessary remedial measures
  • Construction Monitoring: Geotechnical engineers oversee construction projects to ensure that geotechnical recommendations are properly implemented
  • They monitor excavation, foundation construction, and other geotechnical aspects, providing guidance and addressing any geotechnical issues that arise
